\[\begin{split}\sigma=\sum_{j\in\mathcal{A}_{i}\cap\mathcal{I}_{1}} \frac{1}{\|\bm{X}_{i}-\bm{X}_{j}\|_{F}}&\geq\sum_{j\in\mathcal{A}_{i} \cap\mathcal{I}_{1}}\frac{1}{\|\bm{X}_{i}-\bm{I}\|_{F}+\|\bm{X}_{j}-\bm{I}\|_ {F}}\\ &\geq\frac{4}{5\delta_{k}}|\mathcal{A}_{i}\cap\mathcal{I}_{1}|= \frac{4(1-2\epsilon)npq}{5\delta_{k}}.\end{split}\]where the second inequality holds because \(\|\bm{X}_{i}-\bm{I}\|_{F}+\|\bm{X}_{j}-\bm{I}\|_{F}\leq 5\delta_{k}/4\) as \(j\in\mathcal{I}_{1}\). It implies

